      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p> The papers of William Howard Taft III, ambassador to Ireland, son of
		  Senator Robert A. Taft and grandson of President William H. Taft, were given to
		  the Library of Congress in 1996 by his wife, Barbara Taft.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <processinfo encodinganalog="583">
         <head>Processing History</head>
         <p>The papers of William Howard Taft were arranged and described in 1997.
		  The collection was revised in 2009.</p>
      </processinfo>
      <userestrict encodinganalog="540">
