      </userestrict>
      <accessrestrict encodinganalog="506 0">
         <head>Access and Restrictions</head>
         <p>The papers of William Howard Taft are open to research. Researchers
		  are advised to contact the Manuscript Reading Room prior to visiting. Many
		  collections are stored off-site and advance notice is needed to retrieve these
		  items for research use.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite encodinganalog="524">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the
		  following information: Container number, William Howard Taft Papers, Manuscript
		  Division, Library of Congress, Washington, D.C. </p>
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p> The papers of William Howard Taft III (7 Aug. 1915-1991) span the
		  years 1915-1953 and consist of correspondence primarily between Taft and his
		  parents, Robert A. Taft and Martha Wheaton Bowers Taft, especially during his
		  school years at the Taft School in Watertown, Connecticut, at Yale University,
		  and as a graduate student at Princeton University. Also included are three
		  letters from Horace D. Taft and one letter of congratulations from William H.
		  Taft to his son, Robert A. Taft, upon the birth of William Howard Taft III. In
		  these papers, Robert and Martha Taft's son was called William Howard Taft II
		  during the 1930s but by 1947 was addressed as William Howard Taft III.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Papers</head>
         <p>This collection is arranged alphabetically by name of correspondent
		  and therein chronologically.</p>
